      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "FREIGHT EXPRESS (1) goes very well at the distance with five wins and a placing from seven starts. Hit the frame latest (29.90) when second at Wentworth Park in a Grade 5. Makes strong appeal on best. SHOT OF MAGIC (7) ran below his best last time finishing fourth (22.78) over 400m at Maitland in a Grade 4/5. Form here at this distance is sound. Boasts three wins from three starts out of this box. Cannot be left out. TINO BANNER (8) wasn't far away at the finish when 4th and beaten only 4.5 lengths (22.78) at Bulli. Form here at the trip sound including six wins. Good beginner but will need a little luck early crossing from an outside draw. Great chance to atone. LOCHINVAR CHIRON (2) looks a chance coming off a four-and-a-half months layoff.",
